	bibsource = {dblp computer science bibliography, https://dblp.org},
	abstract = {The rapid development of the Internet of vehicles (IoV) has promoted the popularization of the application of intelligent transportation system, and the high matching selection degree between electric vehicle users and charging piles in the IoV can significantly improve the user’s charging experience. Therefore, the construction of intelligent charging service selections is crucial to the intelligent transportation system. This paper proposes an intelligent vehicle charging selection scheme under the cross-area service mode of IoV blockchain based on TOPSIS model, comprehensively evaluates the object weight of key factors of vehicle charging service and the subject tendency of users to each factor, and recommends the optimal charging pile to meet the subjective needs of users. Compared with similar work, it has a great improvement in shortening the driving distance to a charging pile, reducing the time spent waiting for charging and reducing the charging cost.}
